  "slug": "lemon-blueberry-traybake",
  "title": "Lemon and blueberry traybake",
  "subtitle": "Butter sponge with lemon drizzle and blueberries",
  "excerpt": "A light, moist butter sponge packed with blueberries, sharpened with lemon zest, and finished with a lemon drizzle icing. Works with fresh or frozen blueberries. One bowl, one tin.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "The lemon-blueberry traybake is a contemporary British domestic recipe documented in home baking from the late twentieth century. The combination of sharp lemon and sweet blueberry in a butter sponge is now a standard of British home baking and café menus.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A simple butter sponge technique: cream, add eggs, fold in flour, stir in the berries. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Fresh or frozen blueberries",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaegpy50000hsv4cfjew4jf"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " both work; if using frozen, don't thaw them. Toss the berries in a tablespoon of flour before folding in to help prevent them sinking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
