      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan. Grease a 20×30 cm tin and line with baking paper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{free-range-eggs}} one at a time, then the lemon zest from the {{lemons}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}}, then stir in the {{whole-milk}}. Toss the {{blueberries}} in 1 tablespoon of flour, then fold into the batter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 28 to 32 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread the batter into the tin. Bake for 28 to 32 minutes until a skewer comes out clean and the cake has pulled slightly from the sides. Cool in the tin for 20 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ice and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{icing-sugar}} with enough lemon juice from the {{lemons}} to make a thick, pourable icing. Pour over the still-warm cake and spread to the edges. Leave to set for 20 minutes before cutting into squares.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
